    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A substance that adds oxygen or removes hydrogen in chemical reaction with another compound. Used as bleaches that whiten or decolorize in conjunction with oxidizing agents. Examples of reducing agents include: sulfites, bisulfites, dithionite, and sodium borohydride.</Note_Text>
